job_desc:
Epsilon C5I (www.epsilonsystems.com/c5i), focused on software development and systems engineering for intelligence and combat systems, is seeking a Software Engineer Intern for work in San Diego, CA. If you have a passion for excellence in engineering and enjoy working on challenging projects in a fast-paced, team-oriented environment, then this role is for you!

Summary:

Our software teams employ an Agile Scrum process to rapidly design, code, and integrate capabilities into a mature solution. Work includes development of new capabilities and features, as well as maintenance of the existing product line. We are developing a software applications using JavaScript, HTML and React.

Duties and Responsibilities:
  • Write code to power cutting-edge training systems that provide users with an interactive training solution
  • Utilize engineering skills in mobile development and deployment to generate and improve code and code efficiency
  • Write well-designed, testable and efficient code that meets technical requirements
  • Participate in a highly collaborative team environment, contributing to all phases of the development lifecycle using Agile/SCRUM methodologies
  • Assist in the troubleshooting of code defects and deployment of timely fixes

Required Qualifications:
  • Working toward a Bachelor of Science (BS) degree in Computer Science or a related discipline
  • 0-1 year of experience with Javascript
  • Mobile application development and deployment
  • Knowledge of Agile development methods, including Scrum, automated testing, static node analysis and continuous integration
  • Ability to obtain and maintain a US Government SECRET Security Clearance
  • Pursuant to the various government contractual requirements, all applicants must be U.S. citizens.

Preferred Qualifications:
  • Experience with a Linux-based Operating System
  • User Interfaces development experience
  • Knowledge of software design patterns
  • Familiarity with the following software tools: Jenkins, Git, Android Studio, VS Code

ADA Notations:
  • Regular communication (hearing/speaking).
  • Noise conditions range from very quiet to very noisy.
  • Prolonged use of computer (typing/keyboarding).
  • Frequently required to sit for long periods of time, stand, and walk.
  • Ability to travel by car, air or other means of transportation, if required.
Epsilon Systems Solutions, Inc. and its subsidiaries are proud to be Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action employers, Minority/Female/Disability/Veterans.

job: Backend Compiler Engineer - New College Grad 2023
job_desc:
We are searching for a Backend Compiler Engineer for an exciting and fun role in our GPU Software organization. Our Compiler team is responsible for constructing and emitting the highest performance GPU machine instructions for Graphics (OpenGL, Vulkan, DX) and Compute (CUDA, PTX, OpenCL, Fortran, C++). This team is comprised of worldwide leading compiler engineering experts who provide leading edge performance and capabilities for NVIDIA's current and future complex parallel SIMT architectures. NVIDIA's invention of the GPU 1999 sparked the growth of the PC gaming market, redefined modern computer graphics, and revolutionized parallel computing. More recently, GPU deep learning ignited modern AI — the next era of computing — with the GPU acting as the brain of computers, robots, and self-driving cars that can perceive and understand the world. Today, we are increasingly known as 'the AI computing company'.

What you will be doing:
  • Understand, modify, and improve an NVIDIA proprietary GPU compiler backend written in C++
  • Design and develop new compiler passes and optimizations to produce best-in-class, robust, supportable compiler and tools
  • Work with global compiler, hardware and application teams to oversee improvements and problem resolutions
  • Be part of a team that is at the center of deep-learning compiler technology spanning architecture design and support through functional languages

What we need to see:
  • B.S. or higher degree in Computer Science/Engineering (or equivalent experience)
  • Background in LLVM code generation such as instruction scheduling, software pipelining, register allocation, GlobalISel, TableGen, LLVM IR, and Machine IR (MIR)
  • Excellent hands-on C++ programming skills
  • Strong background in software engineering principles with a focus on crafting robust and maintainable solutions to challenging problems
  • Good communication and documentation skills and self-motivated

Ways for you to stand out from the crowd:
  • Masters or PhD preferred, with 2+ years of compiler code generation experience
  • Experience in developing CUDA, DirectX, OpenGL/Vulkan applications

With competitive salaries and a generous benefits package, we are widely considered to be one of the technology world’s most desirable employers. We have some of the most forward-thinking and hardworking people in the world working for us and, due to unprecedented growth, our exclusive engineering teams are rapidly growing. If you're a creative and autonomous engineer with a real passion for technology, we want to hear from you.
The base salary range is $100,000 - $184,000. Your base salary will be determined based on your location, experience, and the pay of employees in similar positions. You will also be eligible for equity and benefits
NVIDIA is committed to fostering a diverse work environment and proud to be an equal opportunity employer. As we highly value diversity in our current and future employees, we do not discriminate (including in our hiring and promotion practices) on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status or any other characteristic protected by law.
course_desc: The ICT industry is one of the fastest growing industries in the world. job_desc:
A lot's changed over the past few years. 2degrees now has 1.9m customers across mobile and broadband, 1700 employees, coverage in 98.5% of NZ and 58 retail stores.
One thing that hasn't changed though, is 2degrees purpose of Fighting for Fair and our love of doing things differently. We love market disruption, we love our customers, and we REALLY love our people.
If you love a bit of banter, challenging the status quo and doing right by Kiwis, then read on!

Unleash Your Tech Superpowers

Internship Programme - Technology and Digital

As an intern with 2degrees, you will have the chance to learn from experienced professionals, contribute to critical projects and develop essential skills in a dynamic and supportive environment.
We are running our Tech and Digital internships starting mid-November 2023 through to early February 2024 (excluding Christmas closure period). This opportunity will equate to approximately 400 hours of practical experience.
A motivated student, you will be looking for an opportunity to experience a Telco which is challenging the norm and what is perceived as fair, by innovating and pushing boundaries. You will be eager to contribute to interesting projects with a positive attitude and willingness to learn along the way.

Here are some of the opportunities we have available for interns:
  • Cloud & Platform Engineer
  • Systems Analyst (Knowledge Management)
  • Data & Analytics Specialist
  • Developer
  • Technology Analyst (Transition & Quality)
  • Mobile Network Engineer
  • Data Networks Project Coordinator
  • Technical Project Manager
  • Planning Specialist (Network Infrastructure)
……And here's some of the benefits of joining us as an intern:
  • Working for a fairer New Zealand: Join a culture dedicated to making New Zealand a better place to live and work - rare in the telco market.
  • Women in tech Community: Join our active community, supporting talented wahine making a career in technology.
  • Career development: You're our focus. Keep on developing your talents as we support and develop you.
We work flexibly here at 2degrees and that means we are open to flexing the roles we have to suit you! If you are keen to join us as an intern but nothing above tickles your fancy, you can still apply and we'll have a chat about what you're keen on.
course_desc: The 14 week In-Person full immersion program teaches those technologies most in need in the marketplace with a heavy focus on JavaScript and the LAMP stack to become full stack web developers at the conclusion. Our full immersion program is taught by an experienced team of full-time instructors, staff & career services department. The curriculum has been honed to provide the technical skills to compete for a job in the marketplace and so that graduates can learn any chosen technology. In addition, the program focuses on the soft skills related to web development so that students not only have a polished portfolio of projects but the presentation and interview skills to effectively compete in the marketplace. In summary, students learn by doing with the support of instructors that have been successful commercial developers for many years.
ment_desc: I am a seasoned technical consultant with over 10 years of experience in roles such as software engineer, systems architect, and project manager. I offer mentorship to aspiring professionals, providing guidance on technical skills development, career planning, and professional growth. job_desc:
About Tencent

Tencent is a world-leading internet and technology company that develops innovative products and services to improve the quality of life of people around the world. Founded in 1998 ，our guiding principle is to use technology for good. We are not only a major video game publisher in the world, we also produce other high-quality digital content, enriching interactive entertainment experiences for people around the globe. We offer a range of services such as cloud computing, advertising, FinTech, and other enterprise services to support our clients' digital transformation and business growth.

About Lightspeed

Summary

LightSpeed Studios is one of the world’s most innovative and successful game developers. With team across China, United States, Singapore, Canada, United Kingdom, France, Japan, South Korea, New Zealand, and United Arab Emirates. We are expanding to more countries.

Founded in 2008, LightSpeed Studios has created over 50 games across multiple platforms and genres for over 4 billion registered users. It is the co-developer of worldwide hits PUBG MOBILE, Apex Legends Mobile, and League of Legends: Wild Rift (Chinese Version).

LightSpeed Tech Center is a centralized platform for LightSpeed Studios, including game engine, audio, QA, AI, tech partnership, research & development, and other tech-related teams.
  • Responsible for communication with overseas partners, inncluding requirements communication and alignment, meeting organization, meeting translation and adhoc requests.;
  • Responsible for R&D process management, including process monitoring, quality control and risk control etc.
Requirements:
  • English can be used as a working language and able to communicate with overseas partner with result driven attitude;
  • Solid communication and coordination skills, can handle complex inter-department cooperation;
  • Passion for video games
  • Work Mode: Onsite

ment_desc: Hi there! I'm Cardi, a skilled UI/UX Developer with several years of hands-on experience in crafting intuitive and visually appealing user interfaces. job_desc:
Interested in joining Auckland’s pre-eminent, multi award winning, specialist commercial property law firm based in the PwC Tower at Commercial Bay?

If so, now is your chance.

While you may be happy enough where you are - receiving favourable feedback and being given good opportunities - you are likely to be aware that the next phase of your learning and growth will come by stepping out of the familiar and aligning yourself with leading lawyers working with their clients and team differently to the norm.

As you probably know, TBB provides specialist legal advice to the premium segment of the commercial property sector.

The firm attracts high calibre lawyers at all levels and the Directors lead a high engagement, high performance culture, fostering close working relationships with clients and team, and accelerating career development. What you may not know, is that TBB offers more than that. It offers total immersion into the business of commercial property.

TBB takes a unique approach to their clients to become their partner in business and the Directors will coach you to do this too. Clients actively seek their strategic advice to achieve their goals so you will benefit from exposure to the commercial drivers of transactions. The firm also has an extensive network of property professionals enabling clients to find innovative solutions and the Directors will include you in this also. As you knew, or can now tell, TBB is not your typical, top-tier property practice.

In return, regardless of years of experience, you will offer a good combination of technical and commercial nous, quality property legal experience, (upwards of 2 years), drive, hard work and a natural ability to build enduring relationships. You will be ambitious to continue learning and growing. You will be team oriented and quickly make a trusted colleague. Not least, you will be absolutely dedicated to doing whatever it takes to look after your clients incredibly well.

Interested?

We are talking with people as they approach us (directly please) so we encourage you to get in touch sooner than later, by telephoning or emailing Victoria Fletcher to enquire or express your interest.

021 300 982 / victoria@victoriafletcher.co.nz.
course_desc: Our LLM is designed to provide an advanced level of flexible legal study for both full-time and part-time students. You can study while you work to keep up the momentum or go full-time to get to the next level even faster. Entry to the LLM is available throughout the year providing the flexibility you need to accelerate your career. The LLM also permits cross-disciplinary study in the form of one or two masters courses (up to 30-points) from another faculty at the University of Auckland. It also provides skills in legal research methodology for those without advanced skills in this area. With over 30 taught courses to choose from you can concentrate your study in particular areas of specialisation or study a broad range of legal subjects. The LLM can be undertaken by coursework, research or a combination of both.
ment_desc: Greetings! My name is Jacinda, and I am a dedicated criminal lawyer with a wealth of experience in defending clients in complex legal cases. With over 15 years of practice in the field, I have handled a wide range of criminal matters, including white-collar crimes, drug offenses, and violent crimes. As a mentor, I am committed to supporting aspiring legal professionals who are interested in pursuing a career in criminal law. I can provide invaluable guidance on legal strategy, case preparation, courtroom advocacy, and effective client communication. Drawing from my extensive courtroom experience, I can help you develop strong analytical and problem-solving skills, enabling you to navigate the intricacies of criminal law and effectively represent your clients. Additionally, I understand the emotional and ethical challenges that arise in this field, and I can offer mentorship on maintaining professionalism, managing high-stress situations, and ensuring a fair and just legal process. Together, we will work on honing your legal expertise and building the necessary skills to be a successful criminal lawyer, making a positive impact in the pursuit of justice.

job_desc:
Gateway Lawyers is a boutique law firm based in East Auckland. We pride ourselves that we have a “feel at home” and supportive environment.

The Role

We currently have an exciting role for a Graduate and a Lawyer with at least 2 years or more of experience who wishes to further their career in Property Law. The candidate needs to have a go get attitude and be willing to learn at the same time.

About Yourself

We are looking for a candidate with:
  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills
  • Ability to go that extra mile to meet the clients’ needs
  • Ability to build strong and lasting relationships
  • Ability to adopt to the culture of the firm
  • Top marks in their law degree

The Process

Please email your application to rani@gatewaylawyers.co.nz:
  • CV
  • Covering letter
  • Academic transcript
course_desc: Our Profs (Professional Legal Studies) course is designed to provide you with the practical skills necessary to excel as a new lawyer. By engaging in this program, you will not only enhance your legal expertise but also gain the confidence to tackle real-life legal scenarios effectively. While universities offer a solid theoretical foundation in law, employers also expect new lawyers to possess essential practical skills. At Profs, we equip you with the tools needed to navigate the challenges of legal practice. Throughout the course, you will learn invaluable skills such as interviewing and advising clients, clear communication with colleagues, trial preparation and advocacy on behalf of clients, drafting documents proficiently, conducting research and legal analysis to solve client problems, and negotiating and mediating with confidence. With Profs, you will be fully prepared to embark on a successful legal career.
ment_desc: I am Judge Serena, an experienced and impartial judicial professional with a proven track record of delivering fair and just verdicts. With years of dedicated service on the bench, I have presided over a wide range of cases, including civil disputes, criminal trials, and family matters. As a mentor, I am passionate about guiding aspiring legal professionals in their journey towards becoming competent and ethical judges. I can offer valuable insights on legal analysis, courtroom decorum, effective decision-making, and the interpretation and application of laws. Together, we will explore the nuances of the judicial process, ensuring a commitment to upholding the principles of justice and fairness.
